  <static seed="55" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring145.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{8x^{5}y^{7}z^{9}+16x^{4}y^{7}z^{8}+36x^{3}y^{7}z^{7}}=</m> <fillin characters="31" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>4x^{3}y^{7}z^{7}\mathopen{}\left(2x^{2}z^{2}+4xz+9\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>4x^3y^{7}z^{7}</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{8x^{5}y^{7}z^{9}+16x^{4}y^{7}z^{8}+36x^{3}y^{7}z^{7}}={4x^{3}y^{7}z^{7}\mathopen{}\left(2x^{2}z^{2}+4xz+9\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
